<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Hyrax:
[B]I don't think that any character should be able to hold the camp...I, too, have better things to do with my cleric than sit and ponder the wonders of VI's "Epic" quests, but if I'm willing to take my cleric and my time to camp the spawn, I don't feel that a non-cleric character should have the ability to claim the camp over me.  I guess the way I see it is:

Cleric v. Cleric: First in time, first in right
Cleric v. non-Cleric: Cleric
non-Cleric v. non-Cleric: see "Cleric v. Cleric," above

As I said earlier, if the player (the person, not one of many digital representations) is actually conscious and present in Skyfire but wants to play another character and can log the cleric in if asked, that seems to be fair.  (The wall to the North of the dragon statue is quite safe for clerical camping, barring someone kiting over you of course...)
[/B][/QUOTE]

