<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hyrax</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">(Yes, yes, blue servers only.  If you're PK, then there's probably nothing of interest here.  We know you can kill each other and take the spawn. *grin*)<P>Having just witnessed a rather unpleasant /OOC situation (in which I was not personally involved, thankfully) in Skyfire after the killing of the server's second(?) Ragefire, I thought it might be prudent to poll the cleric community re: acceptable camping manners for this most painful stage of the quest.<P>While we still don't know for sure what the details are on the timing of the Skyfire spawn (reports so far suggest around 130 hours), we do know that there will be conflict over the spawn between clerics.  As I recall from before an EQ vacation I took, back in Sol B it was generally accepted (at least on my server) that in order to claim the camp over another epic-needy cleric, you had to have the cleric him/herself actually present and camping the spot.  This means no level 15 rangers or 59 druids could claim to be holding the camp when a cleric who needs the pearl (now box) shows up.  Personally, if the non-cleric is an alt and can log the cleric back in when other clerics want to watch for Rage, that's good by me, but if a real cleric is willing to spend the time staring at the scenery, then the party claiming to hold the spawn should be willing to do the same with his/her cleric.<P>Thoughts?  I'd much rather be informed of some major change in how this camp is handled now rather than get into an argument with a fellow cleric who just happens to be as freaked out about the quest as I am:)<P>Thanks.<P>------------------<BR>Hyrax<BR>Crusaders of Plilo<BR>Zebuxoruk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">derufin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I keep my gf's Warrior with her Invis BP up at the Ragefire spawn in SF (on her comp).  I guess you could argue against that because it isn't actually me; but it is my account, and I pay for it, so in essence...it is me.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>So you got the 2nd Rage Hyrax? dang :P  and grats! </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hyrax</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ack! Sorry, didn't mean to give any impression that I was involved in the Ragefire incident today...I just bounced home and checked in on the spawn while letting the dog out.  When I logged into SF, the /OOC arguments were already taking place, so I guess Rage was killed just before I showed up.  Curses!  Foiled again!  No noodle for me   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>Hyrax<BR>(edit: missed sig, doubled sig, screw it...forget the sig)<p>[This message has been edited by Hyrax (edited 02-06-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fenla</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just got Ragefire on Emarr, and I kept my monk there (2nd account) FDed for safety. Cleric was camped there too but not online due to the hazards of Skyfire. A lot of people are pulling mobs to the area so I preferred to watch with my monk.<P>Talked to another cleric who showed up, but logged in my cleric to show that I was indeed camping and he ceded the spawn (which came 5 minutes after!)<P>Fenla</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sabit</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oh I wasn't these Hyrax, and I didn't know there was an incident =/<P>Basically I would figure, if you have a toon camping him (fairly close to the spawn point), the camp is yours.  I have better things to do with my cleric then sit at one location for up to 72 hours (well, I guess 72-360 hours now =P).<P>good luck with your noodle Hyrax =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sabit</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">dang, forgot I have a loogin at home and one at work =P<P><---derufin hehe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thurlin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well im afraid that with RF still dropping Naggy loot in Skyfire purely camping him will not be enough....<P>I do believe that if you are lucky enough to be in zone when he spawns, wich you would be if camped of course then its a race against the clock to who gets the force to kill him there first.<P>If Cleric A has camped RF for xx hours, RF spawns but his guild is unable to gather the needed force to kill him within...lets say 1 hour (and that i would believe max) then there is no way he could stop Cleric B that comes by 5 mins after RF spawned and is able to get his crew there within 15 mins and ready to kill.. Well then there is no way Cleric B will leave RF up and wait for Cleric A to get around to kill him..<P>It will get ugly... and only way to regulate this in another way than FFA would be if there was a rotation order on the server much like the Karana Council of Guilds on Karana server wich rotate's wich guilds is next for all the big targets and plane's... Without a similar 'control' that is respected by all the guilds and players on the servers (and KCoG actually is) RF will be FFA im afraid...meaning the first guild who tag's him gets him... <P>Just my thoughts on how it will be... not saying that its the best solution...but reality...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hyrax</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"