f your guild is aggro'd by the dragon after it kills them off, then kill it (not saying you should try for aggro either).<P>If they can't muster another attempt, kill the dragon for yourselves.<P>On our server, the first spawn of RF in skyfire wiped out the guild that was camping him (unprepared? dunno).  A GM came and despawned the dragon so they could CR (which I think is bogus..  it's not a GM's fault if you have a hard CR).  No sense in seeing a spawn wasted like that.<BR>Daxlin</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Metanis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey!  I play on Veeshan.  It would be nice if some 3rd party would moderate and setup a queue for Ragefire, but that isn't going to happen on my server.  Basically, this spawn is "firstest with the mostest" and if the first fail, then you can be sure there will be elements of other guilds which will engage immediately and bring him down.  With reports of 120+ hours (someone at Verant needs to get a f*cking life!) respawn, I'm sure I'm not going to sit there non-stop and camp him.  So I will park a gimp there and check periodically and I'll ask my guild to do the same.  If we catch him up then we will mobilize.  If we get mobilized then we will engage.  If someone else is there then it will get nasty.  I've already been rolled once in Sol B and don't plan on letting any misplaced sense of "honor" stop me from finishing this epic.<P>I didn't design this screwy quest...put the blame where it belongs... thanks a lot Verant.<P>Good luck and good hunting.<P>-Metanis<BR>-59th Cleric<BR>-Dark Dynasty<BR>-Veeshan Server<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">OgreAce</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bah.. Ragefire. When I see someone with a cleric epic, I don't gasp with amazment. It's really not a sign for me of honour or even achievment. What I think when I see a cleric with 